description: From Middle English untauȝt; equivalent to un- +‎ taught.

adjectives.description: untaught (comparative more untaught, superlative most untaught)

examples: My ſcoles are not for unthriftes untaught,For frantick faitours half mad and half ſtraught;But my learning is of another degreeTo taunt theim like liddrons, lewde as thei bee.

entries.meaning: (not comparable) Not taught; not conveyed by means of instruction.
examples: What they used to teach hereNow goes untaught.
